The easist way to install it is with a virtual environment

mkdir ~/projects/
cd ~/projects/
git clone https://github.com/pykaldi/pykaldi
git clone https://github.com/uhh-lt/kaldi-model-server

cd kaldi-model-server

virtualenv -p python3 .
source ./bin/activate

pip3 install numpy pyparsing

Install CLIF and KALDI dependencies
 ~/projects/pykaldi/tools/install_clif.sh ~/projects/kaldi-model-server/bin/python3 && ~/projects/pykaldi/tools/install_kaldi.sh ~/projects/kaldi-model-server/bin/python3

Now install pykaldi
~/projects/pykaldi$ python3 setup.py install

You can test the install with:
~/projects/pykaldi$ python3 setup.py test
